The paper deals with representation learning in hierarchical reinforcement learning, which is a problem at the intersection of several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on developing a notion of sub-optimality of a representation and deriving expressions to optimize representation learning objectives. The paper also involves aspects of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as it deals with goal-conditioned policies and hierarchical structures. Additionally, the paper deals with continuous-control tasks, which suggests a connection to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper mentions the use of videos to demonstrate the results, which suggests a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
